            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " seamlessly, and lose nothing. If your audience is in Substack‚Äôs app, as a writer, you risk losing that audience‚Äôs attention by shifting. You are disincentivised to do so. It's a soft form of lock in, that will grow as the app usage grows ‚Äî if it does. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And so, as positive as the initial buzz is about the app, there are some ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "really",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " big questions in the air. Will it make the writers happy? Will it work for readers?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
